HEADWORD: Hazardable
<hw>Haz"ard*a*ble</hw> <pr>(-⟦adot⟧*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Liable to hazard or chance; uncertain; risky.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Such as can be hazarded or risked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hazarder</ent>⟦br⟧
